Learn How the Universe Works Through Disciplined, Thoughtful Dialogue.

 

The Feynman Technique.

 

Members progress through the Frederic Schuller lectures on theoretical physics. After each lecture, we have a session where you explain things to me.

I profess ignorance of the topic in order to engage in dialogue. I listen, ask questions and poke holes in your explanations so you understand more deeply.

I also invite members to Socratic seminars with 4-5 people.

FAQs

  • How do I join?

    Contact Davide and explain why you want to join. In the meantime, I encourage you to progress through the Frederic Schuller lectures.

  • How much time does it take?

    It depends on how familiar you are with the material. Typically it takes 1-week per lecture. But nothing is stopping you from going faster / slower than that. You book calls whenever you feel ready to explain a lecture. Whether that’s 1 per day or 1 per month or anything in between is up to you.

  • What are the prerequisites for joining the group?

    None. We listen to a lecture series that is very first principles friendly. This is great cause you can ask “why why why” and actually get down to the straight logic. Given enough thinking, everything makes sense.

  • How is this different from university courses?

    Having to explain the concept to somebody else forces you to internalize it. It’s totally different than being lectured to. Not to say similar structures don’t exist in universities. Student seminars, reading courses, learning seminars, directed reading programs are all examples of Feynman technique-based learning environments.

  • Who can join?

    Anybody. So long as you can convince me I should let you in.

  • What will I learn?

    You will build a solid foundation. We go through everything from the ground up. Logic, set theory, topology, manifolds, smooth manifolds, bundles, tensors, differential forms, lie algebras, and more. By the end of the group, you will be able to understand questions like this.
